Anonymous Fri 27 May 2022 18:30:13 No.48057464 Report
Quoted By: >>48057632
>>48056934
Terrible Writing Advice is seriously a Reddit tier recommendation, and it's ironically pretty bad advice to tell people to look at it for advice. To be blunt, it's an entertainment channel and never even directly talks about writing. It takes the piss out of well known tropes. I'm not going to say "common tropes", because it likes to pretend shit happens way more often than it actually does for the sake of its comedy. It's basically just trying to poke holes in things popular fiction did at one point that may or may not have been emulated by copycats.

But watching those videos will teach you nothing about writing. In fact, my whole experience with "booktube" has been total shit. If you want to recommend people stuff on YouTube about writing, just tell them to watch Brandon Sanderson's videos. Yes, he's the meme pick, but he's the only person I can think of who does writing advice who actually has a bunch of successfully published novels to show that he knows what he's talking about. Which is more than what we can say for Mr. Snarky 10 Minute Videos (with 3 minutes of ads).
